Package rooms

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Door
    This class is meant to represent a door.
    Doors are unmoving objects that exist in corners of the room and change rooms when they are touched.
    Each door possessses a DoorDirection member of the DoorDirection enum.
    Item
    This class contains (most) of the information necessary to make an item.
    Level
    This class takes care of level generation and storage.
    It contains a number of static methods to help generate a level, most notably the generateLevel method which generate the entire level.
    The Level class can also have an object constructed of it which contains all of the rooms and enemies and doors and enemies needed to make the game run.
    Room
    This class represents a room in a level.
    Each level is separated up into rooms, all of which share the characteristics of this class.
    This class possesses an ArrayList of EnvironmentMember objects which are intended to be enemy objects.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Door.DoorDirection
    This enum is possessed by the Door class with the intent of giving a direction to any Door which is kind of important in a square room.
    Item.ItemValue
    This enum contains all of the values that an item can have.
